.TH "__nla_reserve_64bit" 9 "__nla_reserve_64bit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__nla_reserve_64bit \- reserve room for attribute on the skb and align it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct nlattr *" __nla_reserve_64bit
.BI "(struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "int attrtype "  ","
.BI "int attrlen "  ","
.BI "int padattr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "skb" 12
socket buffer to reserve room on
.IP "attrtype" 12
attribute type
.IP "attrlen" 12
length of attribute payload
.IP "padattr" 12
attribute type for the padding
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Adds a netlink attribute header to a socket buffer and reserves
room for the payload but does not copy it. It also ensure that this
attribute will have a 64-bit aligned \fBnla_data\fP area.

The caller is responsible to ensure that the skb provides enough
tailroom for the attribute header and payload.
